main event: A single, high-pitch, dull grayish-silver object was observed in the sky near Ashland, Kentucky on May 26, 1953.
interesting points: The object increased in size then diminished in flight, lasting about 30 seconds.
The report states that if it could be considered reliable, there is no definite data and insufficient data for analysis.
The witness was a passenger in a car traveling eastbound on the Kentucky Toll Road when they observed the object.
The report includes a detailed questionnaire for the witness to provide information about the sighting, such as the time, weather conditions, and estimated speed and distance of the object.
The report was part of Project Blue Book, the official U.S. Air Force investigation into UFO sightings.
